title: Argentine President Javier Milei Seeks to Penalize Central Bank Money Issuance
description: Javier Milei, the libertarian president of Argentina, is seeking to stop the issuance of money by the country’s central bank. Milei stated he would send a bill to Congress to penalize issuing money with jail time, explaining that central bank officials approving these movements would be incarcerated.
